What do you get for free?

00:02:41.986 --> 00:02:42.726 A:middle
Free is good, right?

00:02:43.606 --> 00:02:45.276 A:middle
To make the task of coming to

00:02:45.276 --> 00:02:48.366 A:middle
Mac easier, many iOS interfaces

00:02:48.366 --> 00:02:49.596 A:middle
and interactions will

00:02:49.596 --> 00:02:51.526 A:middle
automatically be adjusted to

00:02:51.606 --> 00:02:53.066 A:middle
macOS equivalents.

00:02:54.416 --> 00:02:56.256 A:middle
iOS split views will be drawn as

00:02:56.256 --> 00:02:57.166 A:middle
split views on Mac,

00:02:58.046 --> 00:02:59.416 A:middle
system-provided UIs like the

00:02:59.626 --> 00:03:01.736 A:middle
file browser and activity view

00:02:59.626 --> 00:03:01.736 A:middle
file browser and activity view

00:03:01.976 --> 00:03:03.806 A:middle
will be remapped to platform

00:03:03.806 --> 00:03:04.976 A:middle
appropriate equivalents.

00:03:05.736 --> 00:03:07.926 A:middle
Edit menus and iOS contextual

00:03:07.926 --> 00:03:09.866 A:middle
menus will automatically be

00:03:09.916 --> 00:03:11.796 A:middle
presented as contextual menus on

00:03:12.106 --> 00:03:12.466 A:middle
Mac.

00:03:12.936 --> 00:03:14.896 A:middle
Copy and paste, rich text

00:03:14.926 --> 00:03:17.316 A:middle
editing, and key focus all come

00:03:17.316 --> 00:03:18.406 A:middle
for free as well.

00:03:19.026 --> 00:03:22.586 A:middle
Now in all of these cases, the

00:03:22.586 --> 00:03:25.996 A:middle
mapping between iOS and macOS is

00:03:26.086 --> 00:03:27.456 A:middle
relatively straightforward.

00:03:28.726 --> 00:03:30.996 A:middle
However, there are some key

00:03:30.996 --> 00:03:34.606 A:middle
differences between macOS and

00:03:34.606 --> 00:03:34.706 A:middle
iOS.

00:03:34.706 --> 00:03:35.996 A:middle
Designing an app that feels

00:03:35.996 --> 00:03:37.856 A:middle
appropriate for each platform

00:03:38.216 --> 00:03:39.876 A:middle
involves understanding and

00:03:39.876 --> 00:03:41.676 A:middle
accounting for those differences

00:03:42.046 --> 00:03:43.546 A:middle
in your app.

00:03:44.176 --> 00:03:46.226 A:middle
The biggest and most critical

00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:48.476 A:middle
difference is that iOS was

00:03:48.476 --> 00:03:50.836 A:middle
designed for touch, whereas mac

00:03:51.216 --> 00:03:53.096 A:middle
was designed for keyboard and

00:03:53.096 --> 00:03:54.546 A:middle
mouse input.

00:03:55.196 --> 00:03:57.226 A:middle
Designing for touch involves

00:03:57.266 --> 00:03:58.816 A:middle
offering touch targets that are

00:03:58.816 --> 00:04:00.916 A:middle
larger and easier to access,

00:03:58.816 --> 00:04:00.916 A:middle
larger and easier to access,

00:04:01.296 --> 00:04:02.736 A:middle
especially when you're walking

00:04:02.736 --> 00:04:04.026 A:middle
or moving around.

00:04:05.206 --> 00:04:07.366 A:middle
On Mac, using a trackpad or

00:04:07.366 --> 00:04:09.316 A:middle
mouse provides physical

00:04:09.316 --> 00:04:11.606 A:middle
stability and greater control.

00:04:12.456 --> 00:04:13.986 A:middle
And because pointers are small,

00:04:13.986 --> 00:04:15.716 A:middle
people can target and manipulate

00:04:15.716 --> 00:04:17.505 A:middle
interface objects with greater

00:04:17.505 --> 00:04:18.096 A:middle
precision.

00:04:19.356 --> 00:04:21.166 A:middle
Smaller controls also allow Mac

00:04:21.206 --> 00:04:23.736 A:middle
UIs to have greater information

00:04:23.736 --> 00:04:25.246 A:middle
density or greater control

00:04:25.246 --> 00:04:25.666 A:middle
density.

00:04:26.956 --> 00:04:28.446 A:middle
All iOS devices support

00:04:28.446 --> 00:04:30.036 A:middle
Multi-Touch gestures like pan,

00:04:30.316 --> 00:04:31.686 A:middle
rotate, and pinch.

00:04:32.386 --> 00:04:34.056 A:middle
Some Mac setups don't have

00:04:34.126 --> 00:04:35.096 A:middle
Multi-Touch input.

00:04:35.566 --> 00:04:37.276 A:middle
So, if there's any interactions

00:04:37.276 --> 00:04:39.526 A:middle
in your app or any actions that

00:04:39.806 --> 00:04:41.326 A:middle
rely on gestural input to be

00:04:41.326 --> 00:04:43.086 A:middle
performed, you have to find

00:04:43.086 --> 00:04:44.546 A:middle
alternatives for the Mac.

00:04:46.006 --> 00:04:47.936 A:middle
When an iPhone is held with one

00:04:47.936 --> 00:04:49.646 A:middle
hand in portrait orientation,

00:04:49.946 --> 00:04:51.616 A:middle
placing controls in the middle

00:04:51.616 --> 00:04:52.766 A:middle
or the bottom of the screen

00:04:53.026 --> 00:04:54.766 A:middle
might make them easier to reach.

00:04:55.246 --> 00:04:57.586 A:middle
So -- and the same is true for

00:04:57.586 --> 00:04:59.356 A:middle
iPad in landscape orientation.

00:04:59.356 --> 00:05:00.506 A:middle
People tend to grip on the

00:04:59.356 --> 00:05:00.506 A:middle
People tend to grip on the

00:05:00.506 --> 00:05:03.016 A:middle
sides, so placing controls on

00:05:03.016 --> 00:05:04.716 A:middle
the left or right side may make

00:05:04.716 --> 00:05:05.786 A:middle
them easier to reach there.

00:05:07.126 --> 00:05:09.196 A:middle
Obviously, on Mac, people do not

00:05:09.196 --> 00:05:10.626 A:middle
hold or displace when they use

00:05:10.626 --> 00:05:10.936 A:middle
them.

00:05:11.866 --> 00:05:13.706 A:middle
Placing controls along the

00:05:13.706 --> 00:05:15.416 A:middle
bottom, the left or the right

00:05:15.416 --> 00:05:17.826 A:middle
edges provides no ergonomic

00:05:17.886 --> 00:05:19.096 A:middle
benefit whatsoever.

00:05:20.146 --> 00:05:22.666 A:middle
Every area of the screen is just

00:05:22.666 --> 00:05:25.206 A:middle
as easy to reach as every other

00:05:25.206 --> 00:05:25.476 A:middle
area.

00:05:26.536 --> 00:05:28.156 A:middle
And, speaking of displays,

00:05:28.516 --> 00:05:30.086 A:middle
you'll need to consider how your

00:05:30.086 --> 00:05:32.466 A:middle
Apple look on 1x non-Retina

00:05:32.686 --> 00:05:33.226 A:middle
displays.

00:05:33.926 --> 00:05:35.486 A:middle
Special care must be given to

00:05:35.486 --> 00:05:37.376 A:middle
assure that glyphs in text look

00:05:37.596 --> 00:05:38.826 A:middle
crisp and legible.

00:05:39.466 --> 00:05:43.046 A:middle
Look, I know, we all basically

00:05:43.046 --> 00:05:44.656 A:middle
understand that touch devices

00:05:44.956 --> 00:05:46.496 A:middle
are different from desktop

00:05:46.576 --> 00:05:47.206 A:middle
computers.

00:05:48.216 --> 00:05:49.536 A:middle
But what's less obvious is how

00:05:49.536 --> 00:05:51.106 A:middle
interaction models and design

00:05:51.106 --> 00:05:53.266 A:middle
patterns vary between iOS and

00:05:53.396 --> 00:05:54.086 A:middle
macOS.

00:05:54.846 --> 00:05:57.346 A:middle
These differences are the key to

00:05:57.346 --> 00:05:59.196 A:middle
successfully translating your

00:05:59.196 --> 00:06:01.576 A:middle
iPad app's design to macOS.

00:05:59.196 --> 00:06:01.576 A:middle
iPad app's design to macOS.

00:06:02.616 --> 00:06:05.756 A:middle
So, with that in mind, let's get

00:06:05.756 --> 00:06:07.496 A:middle
into the details about how to

00:06:07.496 --> 00:06:08.766 A:middle
design iPad apps for Mac.

00:06:09.616 --> 00:06:11.326 A:middle
As you can see, we have a lot to

00:06:11.326 --> 00:06:11.706 A:middle
cover.

00:06:12.286 --> 00:06:13.686 A:middle
You really may want to take some

00:06:13.686 --> 00:06:14.086 A:middle
notes.

00:06:14.956 --> 00:06:16.406 A:middle
OK. Let's keep going.

00:06:17.296 --> 00:06:19.026 A:middle
Nothing is more critical to an

00:06:19.026 --> 00:06:20.696 A:middle
app's design than how it's

00:06:20.696 --> 00:06:21.446 A:middle
architected.

00:06:22.396 --> 00:06:24.076 A:middle
A logical and intuitive app

00:06:24.076 --> 00:06:25.916 A:middle
structure helps people to find

00:06:25.916 --> 00:06:27.706 A:middle
what they're looking for and it

00:06:27.706 --> 00:06:29.616 A:middle
streamlines navigation.

00:06:30.466 --> 00:06:32.446 A:middle
iOS apps tend to be structured

00:06:32.706 --> 00:06:34.106 A:middle
in one of three ways.

00:06:35.136 --> 00:06:36.616 A:middle
Some apps use tabs for

00:06:36.616 --> 00:06:38.306 A:middle
organizing information into a

00:06:38.306 --> 00:06:40.086 A:middle
small number of top-level

00:06:40.086 --> 00:06:40.576 A:middle
sections.

00:06:41.596 --> 00:06:44.126 A:middle
Some present a top-level list of

00:06:44.126 --> 00:06:45.566 A:middle
sections in a table view.

00:06:46.576 --> 00:06:48.736 A:middle
And some document-focused apps

00:06:49.156 --> 00:06:50.486 A:middle
use -- they use a file/folder

00:06:50.486 --> 00:06:52.266 A:middle
metaphor, might have a document

00:06:52.266 --> 00:06:53.676 A:middle
browser UI at the top level.

00:06:54.426 --> 00:06:55.996 A:middle
The chances are that your app

00:06:56.136 --> 00:06:58.216 A:middle
matches one of these three

00:06:58.216 --> 00:06:58.876 A:middle
archetypes.

00:06:59.826 --> 00:07:01.886 A:middle
The simple path is to find the

00:06:59.826 --> 00:07:01.886 A:middle
The simple path is to find the

00:07:01.886 --> 00:07:04.276 A:middle
closest macOS equivalent and

00:07:04.276 --> 00:07:05.076 A:middle
just use that.

00:07:06.296 --> 00:07:07.936 A:middle
For tabbed apps, you could use a

00:07:07.936 --> 00:07:09.516 A:middle
segmented control in the

00:07:09.516 --> 00:07:10.046 A:middle
toolbar.

00:07:10.906 --> 00:07:12.956 A:middle
If your top-level navigation is

00:07:12.956 --> 00:07:14.606 A:middle
a master list, you can do

00:07:14.606 --> 00:07:16.816 A:middle
nothing and it'll show up as is

00:07:16.946 --> 00:07:19.226 A:middle
on Mac, same thing with a

00:07:19.226 --> 00:07:20.246 A:middle
document browser UI.

00:07:21.366 --> 00:07:23.976 A:middle
A direct translation of your app

00:07:23.976 --> 00:07:26.116 A:middle
structure from iOS to macOS

00:07:26.576 --> 00:07:27.666 A:middle
might be the right way to go.

00:07:28.506 --> 00:07:30.406 A:middle
It provides one key benefit.

00:07:31.346 --> 00:07:33.326 A:middle
It'll make the Mac version of

00:07:33.326 --> 00:07:35.406 A:middle
your app instantly familiar to

00:07:35.406 --> 00:07:36.726 A:middle
the people who are familiar with

00:07:36.726 --> 00:07:38.006 A:middle
your iOS app already.

00:07:39.506 --> 00:07:41.186 A:middle
On the other hand, you might be

00:07:41.186 --> 00:07:42.556 A:middle
missing out on an important

00:07:42.556 --> 00:07:44.336 A:middle
opportunity to streamline

00:07:44.336 --> 00:07:45.066 A:middle
navigation.

00:07:46.436 --> 00:07:49.266 A:middle
On Mac, sidebars are a powerful

00:07:49.266 --> 00:07:50.326 A:middle
navigation tool.

00:07:50.896 --> 00:07:52.756 A:middle
They easily accommodate a large

00:07:52.756 --> 00:07:54.666 A:middle
number of options that can be

00:07:54.666 --> 00:07:56.806 A:middle
grouped and labeled to help

00:07:56.976 --> 00:07:59.136 A:middle
provide additional context and

00:07:59.136 --> 00:08:00.736 A:middle
make them easier to scan.

00:07:59.136 --> 00:08:00.736 A:middle
make them easier to scan.

00:08:01.586 --> 00:08:03.026 A:middle
So, if you currently have a

00:08:03.026 --> 00:08:04.916 A:middle
tabbed app, you could present

00:08:04.916 --> 00:08:06.136 A:middle
those tabs in a segmented

00:08:06.136 --> 00:08:08.866 A:middle
control or you could put them

00:08:08.896 --> 00:08:09.756 A:middle
into a sidebar.

00:08:10.946 --> 00:08:12.526 A:middle
Now, this obviously does not

00:08:12.866 --> 00:08:13.516 A:middle
look great.

00:08:13.736 --> 00:08:15.246 A:middle
It's not a very effective use of

00:08:15.246 --> 00:08:16.076 A:middle
screen space.

00:08:16.686 --> 00:08:18.736 A:middle
But if those four tabs have

00:08:18.876 --> 00:08:21.006 A:middle
subsections, you can display

00:08:21.006 --> 00:08:22.616 A:middle
those subsections in line.

00:08:23.446 --> 00:08:25.356 A:middle
This greatly flattens an app's

00:08:25.406 --> 00:08:27.346 A:middle
hierarchy and allows people to

00:08:27.476 --> 00:08:29.366 A:middle
move directly between

00:08:29.366 --> 00:08:30.136 A:middle
subsections.

00:08:30.736 --> 00:08:32.126 A:middle
It can even allow people to

00:08:32.126 --> 00:08:34.306 A:middle
customize these items to their

00:08:34.306 --> 00:08:34.726 A:middle
needs.

00:08:35.885 --> 00:08:37.696 A:middle
As we saw before, if your app

00:08:37.696 --> 00:08:39.936 A:middle
has top-level list or table view

00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:42.126 A:middle
for navigating between sections,

00:08:42.736 --> 00:08:44.126 A:middle
that translates directly.

00:08:44.546 --> 00:08:45.986 A:middle
Split views are the way to get a

00:08:45.986 --> 00:08:46.996 A:middle
sidebar on Mac.

00:08:47.756 --> 00:08:49.176 A:middle
You just enable the translucent

00:08:49.176 --> 00:08:50.446 A:middle
background and you're good to

00:08:50.446 --> 00:08:50.666 A:middle
go.

00:08:51.846 --> 00:08:53.876 A:middle
And lastly, if your iOS app

00:08:53.876 --> 00:08:55.406 A:middle
shows a document browser at the

00:08:55.406 --> 00:08:57.386 A:middle
top level, you can use a sidebar

00:08:57.386 --> 00:08:59.766 A:middle
for providing persistent access

00:09:00.086 --> 00:09:02.066 A:middle
to folders or for displaying

00:09:02.286 --> 00:09:03.336 A:middle
saved searches.

00:09:04.376 --> 00:09:06.276 A:middle
If you use a sidebar, there are

00:09:06.276 --> 00:09:07.566 A:middle
two things to keep in mind.

00:09:08.876 --> 00:09:10.946 A:middle
First, sidebars are providing

00:09:10.946 --> 00:09:12.656 A:middle
access to locations within your

00:09:12.656 --> 00:09:15.366 A:middle
app or collections of documents.

00:09:16.276 --> 00:09:17.666 A:middle
They're not really meant for

00:09:17.666 --> 00:09:19.146 A:middle
showing the documents or other

00:09:19.146 --> 00:09:20.996 A:middle
kinds of content directly.

00:09:22.246 --> 00:09:24.106 A:middle
Second, the sidebar plays an

00:09:24.106 --> 00:09:26.136 A:middle
important role in helping people

00:09:26.136 --> 00:09:27.926 A:middle
understand which window or app

00:09:28.256 --> 00:09:29.646 A:middle
has key focus.

00:09:30.486 --> 00:09:32.616 A:middle
Glyphs, selection highlights and

00:09:32.686 --> 00:09:34.036 A:middle
the sidebar background itself

00:09:34.306 --> 00:09:35.726 A:middle
are stylized to appear

00:09:35.726 --> 00:09:37.456 A:middle
translucent when the current

00:09:37.456 --> 00:09:38.676 A:middle
window is active.

00:09:39.416 --> 00:09:40.856 A:middle
This effect goes away when the

00:09:40.856 --> 00:09:42.286 A:middle
window becomes inactive.

00:09:43.076 --> 00:09:44.806 A:middle
Knowing which window is going to

00:09:44.806 --> 00:09:46.816 A:middle
respond to keyboard input is

00:09:46.816 --> 00:09:47.896 A:middle
super important.

00:09:48.816 --> 00:09:50.716 A:middle
To support this effect, use a

00:09:50.716 --> 00:09:51.896 A:middle
translucent background.

00:09:52.256 --> 00:09:53.826 A:middle
Don't fill the sidebar in with a

00:09:53.826 --> 00:09:55.886 A:middle
solid color or an image or

00:09:55.886 --> 00:09:57.346 A:middle
pattern or anything like that.

00:09:58.036 --> 00:09:59.806 A:middle
For selection highlights, use

00:09:59.806 --> 00:10:01.266 A:middle
the system selection color

00:09:59.806 --> 00:10:01.266 A:middle
the system selection color

00:10:01.566 --> 00:10:02.856 A:middle
rather than a custom color or

00:10:02.856 --> 00:10:04.286 A:middle
like an app tint color.

00:10:05.176 --> 00:10:07.146 A:middle
And in general, you should use

00:10:07.146 --> 00:10:08.466 A:middle
template images that have a

00:10:08.466 --> 00:10:10.666 A:middle
vibrancy effect applied rather

00:10:10.666 --> 00:10:12.646 A:middle
than full color images unless

00:10:12.646 --> 00:10:13.416 A:middle
it's necessary.

00:10:14.626 --> 00:10:17.386 A:middle
OK. Next, let's talk about

00:10:17.386 --> 00:10:17.906 A:middle
toolbars.

00:10:18.806 --> 00:10:20.256 A:middle
Toolbars are commonplace on the

00:10:20.256 --> 00:10:20.556 A:middle
Mac.

00:10:20.556 --> 00:10:22.546 A:middle
And chances are, you'll want to

00:10:22.546 --> 00:10:24.066 A:middle
use one for your app.

00:10:24.466 --> 00:10:26.296 A:middle
Placing controls into a toolbar

00:10:26.556 --> 00:10:28.026 A:middle
makes them more discoverable.

00:10:28.026 --> 00:10:29.896 A:middle
And it leads to a more stable

00:10:29.896 --> 00:10:31.086 A:middle
user experience.

00:10:31.946 --> 00:10:33.726 A:middle
Toolbars create a top-down

00:10:33.756 --> 00:10:35.246 A:middle
information flow which is the

00:10:35.246 --> 00:10:36.736 A:middle
norm for Mac apps.

00:10:37.596 --> 00:10:39.796 A:middle
If your iPad app has any actions

00:10:39.796 --> 00:10:41.036 A:middle
that are located along the

00:10:41.086 --> 00:10:44.446 A:middle
bottom edge of the screen, doing

00:10:44.446 --> 00:10:46.126 A:middle
the same thing in a Mac window

00:10:46.126 --> 00:10:47.476 A:middle
can be very problematic.

00:10:48.176 --> 00:10:49.686 A:middle
Mac windows are draggable.

00:10:50.296 --> 00:10:51.806 A:middle
The bottom edge of Mac windows

00:10:51.806 --> 00:10:54.846 A:middle
might be dragged out of you, or

00:10:54.846 --> 00:10:55.626 A:middle
below the dock.

00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:58.056 A:middle
Clearly this leads to some

00:10:58.196 --> 00:10:59.336 A:middle
usability issues.

00:11:00.536 --> 00:11:01.926 A:middle
When putting actions into the

00:11:01.926 --> 00:11:03.806 A:middle
toolbar, keep in mind that a

00:11:03.806 --> 00:11:05.696 A:middle
toolbar's contents don't change

00:11:06.006 --> 00:11:07.786 A:middle
based on what area of an app

00:11:07.986 --> 00:11:08.996 A:middle
someone is in.

00:11:09.626 --> 00:11:10.886 A:middle
If they can't be used in a

00:11:10.886 --> 00:11:12.976 A:middle
certain area of the app, they'll

00:11:12.976 --> 00:11:13.826 A:middle
be disabled.

00:11:14.976 --> 00:11:16.666 A:middle
But toolbar action should only

00:11:16.666 --> 00:11:18.586 A:middle
really get disabled if nothing

00:11:18.586 --> 00:11:20.096 A:middle
is selected for them to act

00:11:20.096 --> 00:11:20.566 A:middle
upon.

00:11:21.166 --> 00:11:23.266 A:middle
So, if actions are only relevant

00:11:23.266 --> 00:11:25.186 A:middle
in specific areas of your app,

00:11:25.656 --> 00:11:27.236 A:middle
they probably should not be in

00:11:27.236 --> 00:11:27.766 A:middle
the toolbar.

00:11:28.996 --> 00:11:30.626 A:middle
That said, you can provide

00:11:30.626 --> 00:11:32.806 A:middle
contextually relevant actions in

00:11:32.806 --> 00:11:33.766 A:middle
an action menu.

00:11:34.286 --> 00:11:35.826 A:middle
Action menus can dynamically

00:11:35.826 --> 00:11:37.656 A:middle
change based on the current view

00:11:37.926 --> 00:11:38.816 A:middle
or selection.

00:11:39.706 --> 00:11:41.086 A:middle
For example, with a file

00:11:41.086 --> 00:11:42.796 A:middle
selected in a Finder window, the

00:11:43.066 --> 00:11:44.766 A:middle
action menu includes actions

00:11:44.766 --> 00:11:45.996 A:middle
that can be performed on the

00:11:45.996 --> 00:11:46.516 A:middle
file.

00:11:46.556 --> 00:11:48.806 A:middle
And with nothing selected, the

00:11:48.806 --> 00:11:50.526 A:middle
action menu contains commands

00:11:50.776 --> 00:11:52.196 A:middle
that can be performed on the

00:11:52.196 --> 00:11:53.726 A:middle
current folder that we're

00:11:53.726 --> 00:11:54.176 A:middle
viewing.

00:11:54.466 --> 00:11:57.236 A:middle
Now, action menus are not meant

00:11:57.236 --> 00:11:58.076 A:middle
to be a catchall.

00:11:58.396 --> 00:12:00.146 A:middle
So be selective about what you

00:11:58.396 --> 00:12:00.146 A:middle
So be selective about what you

00:12:00.146 --> 00:12:01.076 A:middle
put into them.

00:12:02.126 --> 00:12:04.286 A:middle
OK. Next, let's talk about

00:12:04.286 --> 00:12:04.706 A:middle
layout.

00:12:05.706 --> 00:12:07.446 A:middle
Mac windows are much, much,

00:12:07.446 --> 00:12:09.416 A:middle
much, much larger than iPads.

00:12:10.126 --> 00:12:11.476 A:middle
You'll have much more space to

00:12:11.476 --> 00:12:13.336 A:middle
play with, especially in full

00:12:13.336 --> 00:12:13.866 A:middle
screen.

00:12:14.506 --> 00:12:16.106 A:middle
But taking advantage of all of

00:12:16.106 --> 00:12:17.986 A:middle
that space requires a layout

00:12:17.986 --> 00:12:20.176 A:middle
that's optimized for iPad.

00:12:21.066 --> 00:12:23.056 A:middle
Now, some iPad layouts are just

00:12:23.216 --> 00:12:25.116 A:middle
blown-up iPhone interfaces,

00:12:25.656 --> 00:12:27.986 A:middle
which looks really bad on an

00:12:27.986 --> 00:12:28.606 A:middle
iPad.

00:12:28.606 --> 00:12:31.626 A:middle
And it looks even worse on a Mac

00:12:31.626 --> 00:12:33.476 A:middle
especially in full screen.

00:12:34.606 --> 00:12:36.646 A:middle
Optimizing your layouts for iPad

00:12:36.646 --> 00:12:38.856 A:middle
and Mac requires special

00:12:38.856 --> 00:12:39.826 A:middle
consideration.

00:12:40.736 --> 00:12:42.576 A:middle
For both devices, readable

00:12:42.576 --> 00:12:44.476 A:middle
content margins keep text lines

00:12:44.476 --> 00:12:46.296 A:middle
from getting too long so that

00:12:46.296 --> 00:12:47.616 A:middle
they remain readable.

00:12:48.586 --> 00:12:50.196 A:middle
Breaking content into multiple

00:12:50.196 --> 00:12:51.886 A:middle
columns can be a great way to

00:12:51.886 --> 00:12:54.766 A:middle
maximize information density and

00:12:55.066 --> 00:12:56.216 A:middle
using split views or

00:12:56.216 --> 00:12:58.306 A:middle
master-detail views is a great

00:12:58.306 --> 00:13:00.826 A:middle
way to utilize a wider display.

00:12:58.306 --> 00:13:00.826 A:middle
way to utilize a wider display.

00:13:01.916 --> 00:13:03.156 A:middle
Split views streamline

00:13:03.156 --> 00:13:05.566 A:middle
navigation by simultaneously

00:13:05.566 --> 00:13:07.556 A:middle
displaying a list of objects and

00:13:07.556 --> 00:13:09.546 A:middle
details about that object which

00:13:09.546 --> 00:13:11.516 A:middle
reduces the need to navigate

00:13:11.516 --> 00:13:13.416 A:middle
into and back out of an app

00:13:13.486 --> 00:13:13.976 A:middle
hierarchy.

00:13:14.886 --> 00:13:16.756 A:middle
If you have a Split View in your

00:13:16.756 --> 00:13:18.776 A:middle
app, it'll work great on Mac

00:13:18.876 --> 00:13:20.086 A:middle
without modification.

00:13:21.126 --> 00:13:22.546 A:middle
Now, this may sound a little bit

00:13:22.546 --> 00:13:24.526 A:middle
strange but making your layout

00:13:24.526 --> 00:13:26.886 A:middle
work great on a Mac is probably

00:13:26.886 --> 00:13:28.706 A:middle
the best way to identify and

00:13:28.706 --> 00:13:30.926 A:middle
address layout issues for Mac --

00:13:31.606 --> 00:13:32.116 A:middle
for iPad.

00:13:32.886 --> 00:13:36.526 A:middle
OK. Moving on to type.

00:13:37.936 --> 00:13:40.676 A:middle
On macOS, the baseline font size

00:13:40.676 --> 00:13:41.516 A:middle
is 13 points.

00:13:42.116 --> 00:13:44.916 A:middle
Most controls and labels use

00:13:44.986 --> 00:13:45.766 A:middle
that font size.

00:13:46.816 --> 00:13:48.956 A:middle
On iOS, the baseline font size

00:13:48.956 --> 00:13:49.906 A:middle
is 17 points.

00:13:50.546 --> 00:13:53.466 A:middle
Showing an iOS app with 17-point

00:13:53.466 --> 00:13:55.096 A:middle
type on a Mac would look totally

00:13:55.096 --> 00:13:55.746 A:middle
out of place.

00:13:56.246 --> 00:13:57.796 A:middle
Text would be way too large.

00:13:58.486 --> 00:14:00.786 A:middle
So, to maintain consistency

00:13:58.486 --> 00:14:00.786 A:middle
So, to maintain consistency

00:14:01.096 --> 00:14:03.546 A:middle
between Mac apps, the system

00:14:03.546 --> 00:14:06.196 A:middle
will scale content areas down by

00:14:06.196 --> 00:14:07.586 A:middle
77 percent.

00:14:08.456 --> 00:14:09.556 A:middle
Seventy-seven percent, of

00:14:09.556 --> 00:14:10.796 A:middle
course, as we all know, I don't

00:14:10.796 --> 00:14:12.266 A:middle
even know if I'm pointing this

00:14:12.266 --> 00:14:14.006 A:middle
out, is 13 divided by 17.

00:14:15.126 --> 00:14:17.166 A:middle
Everything in the main interface

00:14:17.166 --> 00:14:18.856 A:middle
will be scaled uniformly.

00:14:19.596 --> 00:14:20.796 A:middle
This approach means that you

00:14:20.896 --> 00:14:23.676 A:middle
don't have to redesign or recode

00:14:23.756 --> 00:14:26.116 A:middle
every screen for macOS.

00:14:27.206 --> 00:14:29.416 A:middle
But it does introduce a bit of

00:14:29.456 --> 00:14:31.686 A:middle
complexity on the design side.

00:14:32.236 --> 00:14:34.076 A:middle
When creating mock-ups of your

00:14:34.076 --> 00:14:36.116 A:middle
iPad app, you'll want to

00:14:36.116 --> 00:14:38.586 A:middle
recreate that 77 percent scale.

00:14:39.326 --> 00:14:41.066 A:middle
So in Photoshop, for example,

00:14:41.066 --> 00:14:42.666 A:middle
you can put your entire content

00:14:42.666 --> 00:14:44.616 A:middle
area into a smart object and

00:14:44.616 --> 00:14:46.536 A:middle
scale it down to 77 percent.

00:14:46.536 --> 00:14:48.696 A:middle
And you can do similar things in

00:14:48.926 --> 00:14:50.966 A:middle
Sketch, XD and other design

00:14:50.966 --> 00:14:51.356 A:middle
tools.

00:14:52.666 --> 00:14:54.966 A:middle
On macOS, apps tend to only use

00:14:55.256 --> 00:14:56.916 A:middle
a few different font sizes.

00:14:57.876 --> 00:15:01.116 A:middle
On iOS, text styles very much

00:14:57.876 --> 00:15:01.116 A:middle
On iOS, text styles very much

00:15:01.116 --> 00:15:01.996 A:middle
more dramatically.

00:15:02.626 --> 00:15:04.516 A:middle
Text styles, the typographic

00:15:04.516 --> 00:15:06.796 A:middle
system for iOS and they offer a

00:15:06.866 --> 00:15:08.896 A:middle
wide range of size options.

00:15:09.906 --> 00:15:11.846 A:middle
Using some of the smallest size

00:15:11.846 --> 00:15:13.856 A:middle
like footnote, caption one,

00:15:13.856 --> 00:15:15.726 A:middle
caption two, can make text

00:15:15.726 --> 00:15:17.296 A:middle
that's difficult to read on Mac.

00:15:18.346 --> 00:15:20.056 A:middle
Even the Mac size mini is often

00:15:20.056 --> 00:15:20.606 A:middle
too small.

00:15:21.706 --> 00:15:23.396 A:middle
So, just -- you may find that

00:15:23.396 --> 00:15:24.466 A:middle
you need to bump up text a

00:15:24.466 --> 00:15:26.086 A:middle
little bit to keep it legible on

00:15:26.086 --> 00:15:26.216 A:middle
Mac.

00:15:27.256 --> 00:15:29.426 A:middle
And, one final note about type,

00:15:29.996 --> 00:15:31.616 A:middle
macOS doesn't support dynamic

00:15:31.616 --> 00:15:31.856 A:middle
type.

00:15:32.396 --> 00:15:34.356 A:middle
We'll always use the large size

00:15:34.356 --> 00:15:36.166 A:middle
setting, it's just scaled down

00:15:36.386 --> 00:15:37.296 A:middle
77 percent.

00:15:38.436 --> 00:15:41.236 A:middle
OK. Now with iOS, every app has

00:15:41.236 --> 00:15:43.146 A:middle
it in color which is used to

00:15:43.146 --> 00:15:44.446 A:middle
show when elements are

00:15:44.446 --> 00:15:45.966 A:middle
interactive or to highlight

00:15:46.026 --> 00:15:46.846 A:middle
selected items.

00:15:47.766 --> 00:15:49.116 A:middle
Some apps go further by

00:15:49.116 --> 00:15:51.436 A:middle
colorizing content area or bar

00:15:51.436 --> 00:15:52.056 A:middle
backgrounds.

00:15:52.896 --> 00:15:54.636 A:middle
On Mac, things are a little bit

00:15:54.676 --> 00:15:55.146 A:middle
different.

00:15:55.846 --> 00:15:57.716 A:middle
It's common for people to have

00:15:57.716 --> 00:16:00.146 A:middle
lots of open windows with lots

00:15:57.716 --> 00:16:00.146 A:middle
lots of open windows with lots

00:16:00.146 --> 00:16:02.016 A:middle
of content in those windows and

00:16:02.016 --> 00:16:03.486 A:middle
lots of files and folders on

00:16:03.486 --> 00:16:04.146 A:middle
their desktop.

00:16:05.016 --> 00:16:07.346 A:middle
If macOS used color like iOS

00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:09.486 A:middle
apps, the user experience would

00:16:09.486 --> 00:16:11.076 A:middle
be really fragmented and

00:16:11.076 --> 00:16:11.666 A:middle
overwhelming.

00:16:12.786 --> 00:16:14.706 A:middle
Mac interfaces should be more

00:16:14.706 --> 00:16:15.226 A:middle
neutral.

00:16:15.716 --> 00:16:16.826 A:middle
They shouldn't compete with a

00:16:16.826 --> 00:16:18.286 A:middle
content that they present to

00:16:18.286 --> 00:16:18.546 A:middle
people.

00:16:19.636 --> 00:16:20.756 A:middle
What people are -- that's what

00:16:20.756 --> 00:16:22.556 A:middle
people are really interested in.

00:16:23.786 --> 00:16:25.856 A:middle
At the same time, translucency

00:16:25.856 --> 00:16:27.826 A:middle
integrates your app into the Mac

00:16:27.826 --> 00:16:28.556 A:middle
ecosystem.

00:16:29.146 --> 00:16:30.606 A:middle
We all like to customize our

00:16:30.606 --> 00:16:32.026 A:middle
desktop pictures and

00:16:32.026 --> 00:16:34.456 A:middle
translucency lets those desktops

00:16:34.546 --> 00:16:36.856 A:middle
influence how apps look and it

00:16:36.896 --> 00:16:38.966 A:middle
brings them altogether into one

00:16:38.966 --> 00:16:40.466 A:middle
cohesive experience.

00:16:41.586 --> 00:16:43.676 A:middle
Similarly, on Mac, highlight

00:16:43.676 --> 00:16:44.896 A:middle
colors are a personal

00:16:44.896 --> 00:16:45.616 A:middle
preference.

00:16:46.146 --> 00:16:47.566 A:middle
If your app uses a different

00:16:47.566 --> 00:16:49.336 A:middle
color to highlight selected

00:16:49.336 --> 00:16:51.926 A:middle
items, it'll feel really out of

00:16:52.026 --> 00:16:53.726 A:middle
place and it'll be downright

00:16:53.726 --> 00:16:55.306 A:middle
confusing for the people who use

00:16:55.306 --> 00:16:56.306 A:middle
your app.

00:16:57.186 --> 00:16:59.096 A:middle
It's worth pointing out actually

00:16:59.396 --> 00:17:00.966 A:middle
that iOS is becoming a little

00:16:59.396 --> 00:17:00.966 A:middle
that iOS is becoming a little

00:17:00.966 --> 00:17:03.476 A:middle
bit more like macOS with respect

00:17:03.746 --> 00:17:04.136 A:middle
to color.

00:17:05.156 --> 00:17:07.396 A:middle
With multitasking, apps are seen

00:17:07.396 --> 00:17:09.346 A:middle
alongside each other far more

00:17:09.346 --> 00:17:09.866 A:middle
often.

00:17:10.346 --> 00:17:11.826 A:middle
A consistent visual look

00:17:12.185 --> 00:17:14.076 A:middle
provides a unified user

00:17:14.076 --> 00:17:14.766 A:middle
experience.

00:17:15.516 --> 00:17:17.586 A:middle
With Dark Mode, people expect

00:17:17.586 --> 00:17:19.566 A:middle
more control over how apps will

00:17:19.566 --> 00:17:20.876 A:middle
look on their device.

00:17:21.626 --> 00:17:23.016 A:middle
Apps that don't respond to their

00:17:23.016 --> 00:17:24.536 A:middle
personal preference will feel

00:17:24.616 --> 00:17:25.266 A:middle
out of place.

00:17:26.276 --> 00:17:28.606 A:middle
And, tint colors play a smaller

00:17:28.606 --> 00:17:29.426 A:middle
part as well.

00:17:30.266 --> 00:17:32.216 A:middle
Steppers and segmented controls

00:17:32.216 --> 00:17:34.796 A:middle
that used to be tinted are now

00:17:35.156 --> 00:17:36.956 A:middle
neutral with iOS 13.

00:17:38.116 --> 00:17:40.326 A:middle
OK. And one last comment about

00:17:40.326 --> 00:17:40.716 A:middle
color.

00:17:41.516 --> 00:17:43.396 A:middle
As some of you may have heard

00:17:43.396 --> 00:17:45.776 A:middle
already, the system colors on

00:17:45.776 --> 00:17:47.046 A:middle
iOS have been completely

00:17:47.046 --> 00:17:47.666 A:middle
overhauled.

00:17:48.356 --> 00:17:50.346 A:middle
If you use these colors for your

00:17:50.346 --> 00:17:52.586 A:middle
iOS app, they'll get remapped to

00:17:52.586 --> 00:17:55.266 A:middle
macOS equivalents for both light

00:17:55.266 --> 00:17:56.126 A:middle
and dark modes.

00:17:57.236 --> 00:17:59.886 A:middle
OK. Moving on to gestures.

00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:02.256 A:middle
UIKit gestures will

00:18:02.256 --> 00:18:04.686 A:middle
automatically remap to trackpad

00:18:04.686 --> 00:18:05.676 A:middle
or mouse events.

00:18:06.636 --> 00:18:08.726 A:middle
Single tap will be the same as a

00:18:08.726 --> 00:18:09.736 A:middle
mouse-down event.

00:18:11.316 --> 00:18:13.466 A:middle
Long press will be mouse down

00:18:13.706 --> 00:18:14.286 A:middle
and hold.

00:18:14.906 --> 00:18:18.416 A:middle
Pan will be the same as a mouse

00:18:18.416 --> 00:18:18.766 A:middle
drag.

00:18:18.766 --> 00:18:20.946 A:middle
And the swipe gesture will be

00:18:21.056 --> 00:18:23.056 A:middle
remapped to a drag in the proper

00:18:23.056 --> 00:18:23.586 A:middle
direction.

00:18:24.646 --> 00:18:26.596 A:middle
On trackpads, pinching and

00:18:26.596 --> 00:18:28.336 A:middle
rotating will work but they'll

00:18:28.336 --> 00:18:29.806 A:middle
behave a little bit differently.

00:18:30.856 --> 00:18:32.926 A:middle
On the iPad, pinch and rotate

00:18:32.926 --> 00:18:34.696 A:middle
use the middle point between

00:18:34.696 --> 00:18:37.056 A:middle
touches to target objects or

00:18:37.056 --> 00:18:39.276 A:middle
center the rotation and scale

00:18:39.276 --> 00:18:39.956 A:middle
operation.

00:18:40.826 --> 00:18:42.986 A:middle
On Mac, the cursor's location

00:18:42.986 --> 00:18:46.576 A:middle
will be used for these purposes.

00:18:46.676 --> 00:18:48.456 A:middle
Screen edge swipes won't be

00:18:48.456 --> 00:18:50.176 A:middle
remapped for obvious reasons.

