00:22:16.926 --> 00:22:18.366 A:middle
Second to last is contextual

00:22:18.366 --> 00:22:18.796 A:middle
menus.

00:22:19.286 --> 00:22:21.216 A:middle
Contextual menus are the unsung

00:22:21.216 --> 00:22:23.706 A:middle
heroes of Mac app interfaces.

00:22:24.476 --> 00:22:25.656 A:middle
They let people know what

00:22:25.656 --> 00:22:27.376 A:middle
actions can be performed on an

00:22:27.376 --> 00:22:29.516 A:middle
object and they bring actions

00:22:29.686 --> 00:22:31.116 A:middle
right to the pointer which

00:22:31.116 --> 00:22:32.576 A:middle
completely removes mouse

00:22:32.576 --> 00:22:32.946 A:middle
trouble.

00:22:34.216 --> 00:22:36.516 A:middle
On Mac, people basically expect

00:22:36.566 --> 00:22:38.476 A:middle
contextual menus everywhere.

00:22:39.006 --> 00:22:40.656 A:middle
So, it logically follows that

00:22:40.656 --> 00:22:42.396 A:middle
you should add contextual menus

00:22:42.456 --> 00:22:43.226 A:middle
to everything.

00:22:43.926 --> 00:22:45.246 A:middle
Any object in your app should

00:22:45.246 --> 00:22:46.776 A:middle
have an associated contextual

00:22:46.776 --> 00:22:48.536 A:middle
menu that contains the most

00:22:48.536 --> 00:22:50.136 A:middle
commonly performed actions.

00:22:51.256 --> 00:22:53.366 A:middle
If you've added contextual menus

00:22:53.366 --> 00:22:54.896 A:middle
for your iOS app, they'll

00:22:54.896 --> 00:22:56.596 A:middle
automatically be brought to

00:22:56.596 --> 00:22:58.106 A:middle
macOS contextual menus.

00:22:58.656 --> 00:22:59.946 A:middle
And the same is true for edit

00:22:59.996 --> 00:23:00.316 A:middle
menus.

00:22:59.996 --> 00:23:00.316 A:middle
menus.

00:23:01.486 --> 00:23:02.376 A:middle
Whether you're designing

00:23:02.376 --> 00:23:04.386 A:middle
contextual menus from macOS or

00:23:04.386 --> 00:23:06.796 A:middle
iOS, the same basic rules apply.

00:23:07.496 --> 00:23:09.156 A:middle
Here are six quick tips to keep

00:23:09.156 --> 00:23:09.526 A:middle
in mind.

00:23:10.176 --> 00:23:12.176 A:middle
First, avoid overwhelming people

00:23:12.176 --> 00:23:13.246 A:middle
with too many options.

00:23:13.856 --> 00:23:15.176 A:middle
Too many options makes it harder

00:23:15.176 --> 00:23:16.076 A:middle
for people to find what they're

00:23:16.076 --> 00:23:18.086 A:middle
looking for and it leads to

00:23:18.086 --> 00:23:19.616 A:middle
menus that take a long time to

00:23:19.616 --> 00:23:20.026 A:middle
scan.

00:23:20.806 --> 00:23:22.556 A:middle
Focus on the most contextually

00:23:22.556 --> 00:23:23.996 A:middle
-- most relevant functionality

00:23:23.996 --> 00:23:24.436 A:middle
only.

00:23:25.286 --> 00:23:26.676 A:middle
Next, be succinct.

00:23:27.316 --> 00:23:29.306 A:middle
One-word labels are typically

00:23:29.426 --> 00:23:29.966 A:middle
sufficient.

00:23:30.776 --> 00:23:32.396 A:middle
When writing labels, convey

00:23:32.396 --> 00:23:34.556 A:middle
action, use verbs or verb

00:23:34.556 --> 00:23:36.636 A:middle
phrases that suggest what the

00:23:36.636 --> 00:23:38.086 A:middle
results of the action will be

00:23:38.146 --> 00:23:39.036 A:middle
when it's performed.

00:23:39.926 --> 00:23:41.596 A:middle
Also, the order of commands is

00:23:41.646 --> 00:23:42.566 A:middle
very meaningful.

00:23:43.206 --> 00:23:44.566 A:middle
Put the most important stuff at

00:23:44.566 --> 00:23:46.356 A:middle
the top and then group related

00:23:46.356 --> 00:23:47.206 A:middle
items together.

00:23:47.716 --> 00:23:49.536 A:middle
Going one step further, use

00:23:49.536 --> 00:23:50.826 A:middle
separators to make the

00:23:50.826 --> 00:23:52.526 A:middle
relationships between commands

00:23:52.636 --> 00:23:53.356 A:middle
explicit.

00:23:54.446 --> 00:23:56.246 A:middle
Grouping commands together can

00:23:56.246 --> 00:23:58.296 A:middle
be very meaningful and it helps

00:23:58.296 --> 00:24:00.286 A:middle
people skip past entire sets of

00:23:58.296 --> 00:24:00.286 A:middle
people skip past entire sets of

00:24:00.316 --> 00:24:02.026 A:middle
commands when they conceive from

00:24:02.026 --> 00:24:03.606 A:middle
the first one or two that it's

00:24:03.606 --> 00:24:04.556 A:middle
not going to be relevant to

00:24:04.556 --> 00:24:05.296 A:middle
their current needs.

00:24:06.466 --> 00:24:08.446 A:middle
And lastly, use submenus to

00:24:08.566 --> 00:24:10.746 A:middle
control menu length and hide

00:24:10.746 --> 00:24:12.476 A:middle
away actions that aren't

00:24:12.626 --> 00:24:13.006 A:middle
relevant.

00:24:13.846 --> 00:24:15.766 A:middle
Submenus are a classic example

00:24:15.766 --> 00:24:17.046 A:middle
of progressive disclosure.

00:24:17.676 --> 00:24:19.896 A:middle
They simplify decision making by

00:24:19.896 --> 00:24:21.326 A:middle
reducing complexity.

00:24:22.556 --> 00:24:24.896 A:middle
OK. Now the last major

00:24:24.896 --> 00:24:26.616 A:middle
consideration that I'd like to

00:24:26.616 --> 00:24:28.696 A:middle
discuss today are menu bars.

00:24:29.986 --> 00:24:31.956 A:middle
Every app has a menu bar.

00:24:32.876 --> 00:24:34.696 A:middle
Menu bars are core to the Mac

00:24:34.696 --> 00:24:36.996 A:middle
experience, go back all the way

00:24:36.996 --> 00:24:37.986 A:middle
to 1984.

00:24:38.866 --> 00:24:41.136 A:middle
Menu bars were key to what made

00:24:41.136 --> 00:24:43.216 A:middle
computers easy to use.

00:24:44.296 --> 00:24:45.866 A:middle
Designing your app's menu bar

00:24:46.166 --> 00:24:48.046 A:middle
begins with this super fun

00:24:48.046 --> 00:24:48.806 A:middle
exercise.

00:24:49.866 --> 00:24:51.216 A:middle
You write down all of the

00:24:51.216 --> 00:24:52.576 A:middle
actions that a person can

00:24:52.576 --> 00:24:54.866 A:middle
perform in your app and I do

00:24:54.866 --> 00:24:56.736 A:middle
mean all of them and then you

00:24:56.736 --> 00:24:58.496 A:middle
take note of what object or

00:24:58.496 --> 00:25:00.366 A:middle
objects those actions affect.

00:24:58.496 --> 00:25:00.366 A:middle
objects those actions affect.

00:25:01.446 --> 00:25:03.036 A:middle
Not only is this exercise

00:25:03.216 --> 00:25:06.106 A:middle
excruciatingly fun, but it's

00:25:06.246 --> 00:25:07.666 A:middle
also necessary.

00:25:08.816 --> 00:25:10.246 A:middle
Every action that someone can

00:25:10.246 --> 00:25:12.126 A:middle
perform in your app should be

00:25:12.126 --> 00:25:13.576 A:middle
available from the menu bar.

00:25:14.206 --> 00:25:15.526 A:middle
This makes them easier to

00:25:15.566 --> 00:25:17.926 A:middle
discover and lets people assign

00:25:17.926 --> 00:25:19.236 A:middle
keyboard shortcuts to them.

00:25:20.166 --> 00:25:21.346 A:middle
It also makes them more

00:25:21.346 --> 00:25:22.516 A:middle
accessible to people who are

00:25:22.516 --> 00:25:25.306 A:middle
using full keyboard access.

00:25:25.346 --> 00:25:26.736 A:middle
Once you've cataloged all of

00:25:26.736 --> 00:25:28.286 A:middle
those actions, you'll need to

00:25:28.286 --> 00:25:29.516 A:middle
find a place for them to go.

00:25:30.256 --> 00:25:32.556 A:middle
macOS includes a standard set of

00:25:32.556 --> 00:25:35.366 A:middle
menu items -- menu options like

00:25:35.776 --> 00:25:37.486 A:middle
the app menu for commands that

00:25:37.536 --> 00:25:39.666 A:middle
work -- operate on the app, file

00:25:39.666 --> 00:25:40.876 A:middle
menu for commands that operate

00:25:40.876 --> 00:25:42.706 A:middle
on files, edit menu for commands

00:25:42.706 --> 00:25:44.016 A:middle
that operate on the content or

00:25:44.016 --> 00:25:45.716 A:middle
objects within those files,

00:25:46.396 --> 00:25:47.946 A:middle
format menu for formatting text,

00:25:48.686 --> 00:25:50.376 A:middle
view menu for customizing the

00:25:50.376 --> 00:25:52.496 A:middle
appearance of a window, window

00:25:52.496 --> 00:25:54.336 A:middle
menu for commands that operate

00:25:54.336 --> 00:25:55.066 A:middle
on windows.

00:25:55.836 --> 00:25:57.896 A:middle
And help menus are for getting

00:25:57.896 --> 00:25:59.576 A:middle
help and finding commands in

00:25:59.576 --> 00:26:00.306 A:middle
those other menus.

00:25:59.576 --> 00:26:00.306 A:middle
those other menus.

00:26:01.466 --> 00:26:03.486 A:middle
Now, for many of your apps,

00:26:03.896 --> 00:26:05.386 A:middle
these standard menus are going

00:26:05.386 --> 00:26:06.646 A:middle
to be all that you actually

00:26:06.646 --> 00:26:06.996 A:middle
need.

00:26:07.796 --> 00:26:09.936 A:middle
However, it's often necessary to

00:26:09.936 --> 00:26:12.006 A:middle
provide additional custom menus.

00:26:12.816 --> 00:26:14.386 A:middle
If you have a couple of key

00:26:14.386 --> 00:26:17.486 A:middle
object types in your app, with

00:26:17.486 --> 00:26:19.636 A:middle
object specific actions, you

00:26:19.636 --> 00:26:20.736 A:middle
should consider adding a

00:26:20.796 --> 00:26:22.676 A:middle
top-level menu or two for them.

00:26:23.576 --> 00:26:25.076 A:middle
So, for example, in the mail

00:26:25.286 --> 00:26:27.166 A:middle
app, there are two main object

00:26:27.606 --> 00:26:30.386 A:middle
types, mailboxes and messages.

00:26:31.326 --> 00:26:32.556 A:middle
There are a number of actions

00:26:32.556 --> 00:26:33.986 A:middle
that can be performed on those

00:26:33.986 --> 00:26:35.456 A:middle
objects and none of those

00:26:35.456 --> 00:26:36.986 A:middle
actions can be performed on the

00:26:36.986 --> 00:26:38.046 A:middle
other type of object.

00:26:38.746 --> 00:26:40.526 A:middle
So it makes sense to have one

00:26:40.526 --> 00:26:42.776 A:middle
menu button for each of those

00:26:42.776 --> 00:26:43.386 A:middle
objects.

00:26:44.836 --> 00:26:46.586 A:middle
At other times, it's helpful to

00:26:46.586 --> 00:26:48.156 A:middle
organize actions by a larger

00:26:48.156 --> 00:26:49.376 A:middle
workflow that they serve.

00:26:50.126 --> 00:26:51.946 A:middle
In keynote, there are a variety

00:26:51.946 --> 00:26:52.966 A:middle
of different object types that

00:26:52.966 --> 00:26:54.846 A:middle
can be added to a slide and

00:26:54.846 --> 00:26:56.106 A:middle
there's a whole set of actions

00:26:56.106 --> 00:26:57.756 A:middle
for aligning and distributing,

00:26:58.006 --> 00:26:59.416 A:middle
locking them, grouping them,

00:26:59.416 --> 00:27:00.936 A:middle
moving them forward or backward.

00:26:59.416 --> 00:27:00.936 A:middle
moving them forward or backward.

00:27:01.666 --> 00:27:02.986 A:middle
And because all of those actions

00:27:02.986 --> 00:27:05.246 A:middle
affect all of those objects in a

00:27:05.246 --> 00:27:07.046 A:middle
similar way, it makes sense to

00:27:07.046 --> 00:27:09.026 A:middle
put them into a single menu

00:27:09.326 --> 00:27:10.366 A:middle
based on the workflow they

00:27:10.366 --> 00:27:10.726 A:middle
serve.

00:27:12.176 --> 00:27:13.336 A:middle
And once you've determined what

00:27:13.376 --> 00:27:15.106 A:middle
custom menus to include in the

00:27:15.106 --> 00:27:16.996 A:middle
menu bar, you'll need to create

00:27:16.996 --> 00:27:18.046 A:middle
the menus themselves.

00:27:18.956 --> 00:27:20.386 A:middle
All of the tips that I just

00:27:20.386 --> 00:27:21.666 A:middle
shared with you for contextual

00:27:21.666 --> 00:27:24.096 A:middle
menus apply here with one

00:27:24.096 --> 00:27:25.156 A:middle
important addition.

00:27:25.856 --> 00:27:27.646 A:middle
The structure of menu bar menus

00:27:27.646 --> 00:27:28.436 A:middle
is stable.

00:27:28.986 --> 00:27:30.956 A:middle
Commands aren't added or removed

00:27:30.956 --> 00:27:32.716 A:middle
after an app has been launched.

00:27:33.426 --> 00:27:35.276 A:middle
Like toolbar actions, they

00:27:35.276 --> 00:27:36.816 A:middle
disable when they can't be

00:27:36.816 --> 00:27:37.456 A:middle
performed.

00:27:38.556 --> 00:27:40.236 A:middle
A stable menu system helps

00:27:40.236 --> 00:27:42.106 A:middle
people to learn where commands

00:27:42.186 --> 00:27:44.056 A:middle
are, even if those commands

00:27:44.176 --> 00:27:45.656 A:middle
aren't currently available.

00:27:46.516 --> 00:27:48.136 A:middle
And, when someone sees a

00:27:48.136 --> 00:27:49.766 A:middle
disabled command, they learn

00:27:49.766 --> 00:27:51.296 A:middle
that the action that it performs

00:27:52.126 --> 00:27:54.116 A:middle
is not currently possible, which

00:27:54.116 --> 00:27:55.326 A:middle
is actually really useful

00:27:55.326 --> 00:27:55.826 A:middle
information.

00:27:56.666 --> 00:27:59.156 A:middle
And, one more thing about menu

00:27:59.156 --> 00:27:59.566 A:middle
bars.

